Work with Milestones

Milestones help give customers a consistent support experience. Learn about milestone statuses, actions, and recurrence types.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Service Cloud.

When working with milestones, tracking everything is key to success. To view records with milestones:

* Create a work order report using the Object Milestones custom report type.
* Create a case report using the Cases with Milestones custom report type.
* Create list views that filter on milestone fields.

Where Can I View Milestones?

Milestone status displays one of three statuses: 
Milestone actions occur on milestones in an entitlement process. 
When creating a milestone, choose its recurrence type and learn what each means.

Milestones represent required support steps for resolving customer issues. Find out where to use milestones in Salesforce.
Learn how to start and resume milestones and how they work within an entitlement process.
